    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But a \"professional\" cannot understand the poetry of this grief. They would only try to patch the cracks in a vessel that is meant to be shattered. Is it not a more noble thing to accept the end when the heart has truly died? To embrace the stillness rather than dragging this hollow shell through another meaningless dawn? It feels so much more... right. Like a final, beautiful surrender to the night.",
