      "content": "You speak of strength, but you speak from a world of light that I no longer inhabit. You call it a \"path,\" but to me, it looks like the only way to find peace. If a play reaches its final, tragic act, does the audience not find a certain grace in the curtain falling? To linger in the shadow of a broken heart... it feels so weary. So purposeless. Is there truly no dignity in letting the flame go out when the oil has run dry?",
